sequenceDiagram
    participant Dev as Developer
    participant Git as Git Repository
    participant Cachi2 as Cachi2 Prefetch
    participant PyPI as AIPCC PyPI Index
    participant Konflux as Konflux Pipeline
    participant CheckPayload as check-payload
    participant Quay as Quay.io Registry
    participant Operator as rhods-operator
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API<br/>6443/TCP
    participant Dashboard as RHOAI Dashboard
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>(Envoy)
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP
    participant Workbench as JupyterLab / code-server<br/>8888 / 8787 TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Object Storage<br/>443/TCP

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Dev,Quay: Flow 1: Image Build and Publication (Konflux)
        Dev->>Git: Push Dockerfile + lock files<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.3
        Konflux->>Git: Clone repository<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.3 SSH key
        Cachi2->>PyPI: Pre-fetch Python wheels<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
        Cachi2->>Konflux: Mount /cachi2/output/deps/pip
        Note over Konflux: uv pip install --no-index<br/>--find-links /cachi2/output/deps/pip<br/>(Hermetic build - no network)
        Konflux->>Konflux: buildah build (16 Dockerfiles)
        Konflux->>CheckPayload: Validate FIPS compliance
        CheckPayload-->>Konflux: Pass/Fail
        Konflux->>Quay: Push container images<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.3 Registry token
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over Operator,Dashboard: Flow 2: Image Consumption by Platform Operator
        Operator->>Operator: Read manifests/rhoai/<br/>ImageStream YAML (file)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update ImageStreams<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS 1.3 SA token
        K8sAPI->>Quay: Pull image metadata<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.3 Pull secret
        User->>Dashboard: Browse notebook images<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.3 OAuth
        Dashboard->>K8sAPI: List ImageStreams + annotations<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS 1.3 User token
        K8sAPI-->>Dashboard: ImageStream metadata
        Dashboard-->>User: Display notebook choices<br/>with version annotations
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over User,S3: Flow 3: User Workbench Session
        User->>Gateway: Open workbench<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.3 OpenShift OAuth
        Gateway->>KRBAC: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS 1.3 Bearer token
        Note over KRBAC: SubjectAccessReview<br/>against namespace RBAC
        KRBAC->>Workbench: Proxy to workbench<br/>HTTP/8888 or 8787<br/>plaintext (localhost)
        Workbench-->>KRBAC: Response
        KRBAC-->>Gateway: Response
        Gateway-->>User: Workbench UI

        Note over Workbench,S3: Runtime data access (user-configured)
        Workbench->>S3: Read/write data<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>AWS IAM / access key
        S3-->>Workbench: Data response
    end
